<br>
For reference purposes, at 55 I had aquired Innate Runspeed 3.  I then hit level 60 before completing any more AA.<br>
<br>
I am still level 60, have aquired Innate Regeneration 3, Spell Casting Mastery 3, Pet Discipline, and will continue to aquire AA points until I have Elemental Pact and Spell Casting Fury 3.<br>
<br>
My viewpoint here is quite simple.  The game means more than simply becoming more powerful and gaining more levels.  Kunark, Velious, and Luclin were all designed and balanced around a maximum PC level of 60.  I have yet to explore many high level Luclin zones such as Acrylia Caverns, The Deep, Grieg's End, and SSRA Temple.  I very much want to enjoy adventuring in these zones in a fashion that they were intended, not blowing through them as I would if I were to go back to Lower Guk now as a 60th level mage.  I still get more enjoyment from the game by playing in Sebilis than I do in, say, PoD.  The froglok action is fast and furious, with different scenarios and challenges emerging every time I delve into this beautiful dungeon, whereas the PoP experience grind is pull one, kill it, repeat.  It is somewhat unfortunate that the PoP experience rate is nearly an order of magnitude greater than such lovely zones as Sebilis.<br>
<br>
So, regardless of whether or not I can get 5 AA per hour at level 65, I intend to enjoy many of the high level Luclin zones before I become too high a level to enjoy it.<br>
<br>
Erun<br>
60 Mage<br>
E'Ci<br>
